    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory trauma-informed training and standards in the family courts service  ",
        "additional_details": "Trauma responses should not be labelled as mental health issues or illness; they should be recognised as symptoms of abuse \u2013 so, if a victim develops PTSD from domestic violence, it should be recorded and understood as a trauma response caused by harm, not a standalone mental health problem. Current guidance is inconsistently applied; there are huge gaps in professionals\u2019 understanding abuse and mental health. We seek mandatory national standards, and a total reform on all current guidance and training.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to ensure mandatory trauma-informed training and standards for all professionals whose assessments influence decisions in the family courts, including judges, CAFCASS officers, social workers, and court-instructed medical experts.",
